&lt;li&gt;Support Members with a wide range of mental health needs, including anxiety, depression, trauma, and relationship challenges with flexibility to work with members with substance use disorders at times. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear and timely clinical documentation in our electronic medical record (EMR) system&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate care as needed and contribute to a supportive, multidisciplinary environment&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in clinical team meetings and optional case consultations&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to HIPAA and all applicable state licensure regulations&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
